    "media:imagetext": "TWA\nEMPLOYEES' TIMETABLE • DOMESTIC SCHEDULES\nISSUE DATE MAY 3, 1974\nThis is what we're telling our customers:\nEFFECTIVE JUNE 1, 1974 -\nJUNE 14, 1974\n(Except as noted)\nSUPER PLANE. TWA's 1011.\nThis is TWA's wide-body 1011.\nWe're adding more of them\nbecause our passengers say it's our most\ncomfortable plane.\nIn coach all the seats are two across.\nAnd there's a choice of movies on\nmovie flights.*\nYou can store your bag in our carry-on\nluggage compartments.\nAnd in first class, seats swivel so you can\ntalk or dine with friends.\nTWA's wide-body 1011.\nOf all our\ncomfortable planes, we think this is the\none you'll like the best.\n* Additional charge in coach. Movies by Inflight Motion Pictures, Inc.\nWATORM 2-0-4 PRINED IN US.A.\nEMPLOYEES' TIMETABLE NO. 74-6\nCancels Employees' Timetable No. 74-5",
